{{混同|已|巳|1=Snake (zodiac)|lt=Snake (巳)}} {{citation needed|'''十干の一つ'''}} {{十干十二支}} '''Ki''' (己) is the 6th of the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|8=en|ja|十干}}.<ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=746338a778c1326c28e064dfc238d5f40d5be0b4b34cbd5a628d4c817af3433cJmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Tsuchinoto+(%e5%b7%b1)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGFub3NoaWlqYXBhbmVzZS5jb20vZGljdGlvbmFyeS9lbnRyeV9kZXRhaWxzLmNmbT9lbnRyeV9pZD01NTc5MiZlbGVtZW50X2lkPTcxNDQx&ntb=1</ref><ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=39bc19b09043852cb3f39659fd413e4d1ce12d6b5eb2c08296574682c71f8352JmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Tsuchinoto+(%e5%b7%b1)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly9qYXBhbmVzZS13b3Jkcy5vcmcvZW4va2Fuamkvdmlldy83OTQ&ntb=1</ref><ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=b8a08bad34a4a3ecb849614d125872ad9b7a09f4bddf3e4eb32624f3436bced5JmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Tsuchinoto+(%e5%b7%b1)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubmlob25nb21hc3Rlci5jb20vamFwYW5lc2UvZGljdGlvbmFyeS93b3JkLzU1NjM4L2tpLXRzdWNoaW5vdG8tJUU1JUI3JUIxLSVFMyU4MSU4RC0lRTMlODElQTQlRTMlODElQTElRTMlODElQUUlRTMlODElQTg&ntb=1</ref>
== Overview == * The origin of the character "己" has been the subject of various hypotheses, but no definitive theory exists.<ref>{{Citation| author=Ji Xusheng| year=2014| title=Shuowen New Evidence| location=Taipei| publisher=Yiwen Publishing House| isbn=978-957-520-168-5| page=964}}</ref><ref>{{Citation| author=Lin Zhiqiang et al.| year=2017| title=Annotations on "Wenyuan"| location=Beijing| publisher=Chinese Academy of Social Sciences Press| isbn=978-7-5203-0419-1| page=116}}</ref><ref>{{Citation| author=Ge Liang| year=2022| title=Re-discovering Chinese Characters: From Old Knowledge to New Insights| location=Shanghai| publisher=Shanghai Calligraphy and Painting Press| isbn=978-7-5479-2884-4| page=106}}</ref> The use of "己" to denote the sixth position in the Ten Stems is a case of {{ill|phonetic loan|ja|仮借}}. * Although visually similar to 已 (i, "already") and {{ill|巳|ja|巳|1=Snake (zodiac)|lt=Snake (巳)}} (shi, "serpent"), these are entirely different characters with distinct meanings and origins. A mnemonic for this is "Ko-ki sounds for 'tsuchinoto', different from 'isude' and 'shimi'." * When used for ranking, "己" signifies the sixth position, though it is rarely used beyond this context. * Years ending in the digit 9 in the {{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|西暦}} are Ki years. The alternate name for Ki years is '''Tuwei''' (or '''Tu Wei''').<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ancient Names and Explanations of the Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08}}</ref> * In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物}}, "Ki" is used in names for compounds containing six carbon atoms, such as {{ill|hexane|ja|ヘキサン}} and {{ill|hexyl group|ja|ヘキシル基}}. * The opposite counterpart in the Ten Stems cycle is {{ill|Kō|ja|甲|1=Kinoe (甲)}}. * The {{ill|lucky direction|ja|恵方|3=歳徳神|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction}} (Eho) for Ki is slightly east of northeast (75 degrees).
