== Overview == * The origin of the character "己" has been the subject of various hypotheses, but no definitive theory exists.<ref>{{Citation| author=Ji Xusheng| year=2014| title=Shuowen New Evidence| location=Taipei| publisher=Yiwen Publishing House| isbn=978-957-520-168-5| page=964|qq=}}</ref><ref>{{Citation| author=Lin Zhiqiang et al.| year=2017| title=Annotations on "Wenyuan"| location=Beijing| publisher=Chinese Academy of Social Sciences Press| isbn=978-7-5203-0419-1| page=116|qq=}}</ref><ref>{{Citation| author=Ge Liang| year=2022| title=Re-discovering Chinese Characters: From Old Knowledge to New Insights| location=Shanghai| publisher=Shanghai Calligraphy and Painting Press| isbn=978-7-5479-2884-4| page=106|qq=}}</ref> The use of "己" to denote the sixth position in the Ten Stems is a case of {{ill|phonetic loan|ja|仮借|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/phonetic loan|qq=}}. * Although visually similar to 已 (i, "already") and {{ill|巳|ja|巳|1=Snake (zodiac)|lt=Snake (巳)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/巳|13=User:Immanuelle/Snake (zodiac)|qq=}} (shi, "serpent"), these are entirely different characters with distinct meanings and origins. A mnemonic for this is "Ko-ki sounds for 'tsuchinoto', different from 'isude' and 'shimi'." * When used for Ranking, "己" signifies the sixth position, though it is rarely used beyond this context. * Years ending in the digit 9 in the {{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|西暦|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=西暦|4=zh|5=公元|6=es|7=Era común|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|qq=}} are Ki years. The alternate name for Ki years is '''Tuwei''' (or '''Tu Wei''').<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ancient Names and Explanations of the Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08|qq=}}</ref> * In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chinese chemical nomenclature|qq=}}, "Ki" is used in names for compounds containing six carbon atoms, such as {{ill|hexane|ja|ヘキサン|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/hexane|qq=}} and {{ill|hexyl group|ja|ヘキシル基|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/hexyl group|qq=}}. * The opposite counterpart in the Ten Stems cycle is {{ill|Kō|ja|甲|1=Kinoe (甲)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kō|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinoe (甲)|qq=}}. * The {{ill|lucky direction|ja|恵方|3=歳徳神|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|qq=}} (Eho) for Ki is slightly east of northeast (75 degrees). ==Sexagenary cycles containing Tsuchinoto (己)==
