website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08|qq=}}</ref> * In [[:en:Chemical compound|Chinese chemical nomenclature]], "Ki" is used in names for compounds containing six carbon atoms, such as [[:en:Hexane|hexane]] and {{ill|hexyl group|ja|ヘキシル基|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/hexyl group|qq=}}. * The opposite counterpart in the Ten Stems cycle is {{ill|Kō|ja|甲|1=Kinoe (甲)|lt=Kinoe (甲)|2=ja|3=甲|4=zh|5=甲|1=Kinoe (甲)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kō|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinoe (甲)|qq=}}. ==Days of Tsuchinoto (己)== ==Sexagenary cycles containing Tsuchinoto (己)==
